Datasets: example algorithm outputs

Source: R/dats-patter.R
datasets-algorithms.Rd

These functions load example outputs from key patter functions. They are included in the package to streamline function examples and tests.

dat_obs()

dat_pff()

dat_pfbk()

dat_pfp()

dat_coa()

Source

For full details on the algorithm parameters used to generate these datasets, see https://github.com/edwardlavender/patter/blob/main/data-raw/003-add-data-algorithms.R.

Details

  • dat_pff() reads an example output from pf_setup_obs();

  • dat_pff() reads an example output from pf_forward();

  • dat_pfbk() reads an example output from pf_backward_killer();

  • dat_pfp() reads an example output from pf_path();

  • dat_coa() reads an example output from coa();

Author

Edward Lavender
